    • Constructor Detail

      • Gcoder

        public Gcoder(PApplet theParent,
              java.lang.String _outputFile,
              float _PHYSICALLIMITX,
              float _PHYSICALLIMITY,
              float _neutralOffsetZ,
              float _contactOffsetZ,
              float _canvasOriginX,
              float _canvasOriginY,
              float _canvasWidth,
              float _canvasHeight)
        The constructor for initialization of the library.
        Parameters:
        theParent - the parent PApplet
        _outputFile - the output file of the generated gcode
        _PHYSICALLIMITX - the physical maximum x of the printer ( = 300 mm for the CR10)
        _PHYSICALLIMITY - the physical maximum y of the printer ( = 300 mm for the CR10)
        _neutralOffsetZ - the z amplitude during the elevation or the descent of the pen
        _canvasOriginX - the origin X of the sketch on the printer
        _canvasOriginY - the origin Y of the sketch on the printer
        _canvasWidth - the width of the printing sketch
        _canvasHeight - the height of the printing sketch

      • adjustPaintingZ

        public void adjustPaintingZ(float _pushFactor)
        Command to add just a little more pression to the pen. In mm, the amplitude of descent is add according to the value i.e. addMorePush(.1) will descent the pen of .1mm more.
        Parameters:
        _pushFactor - value in mm. Must be between -1 and 1 mm.

      • drawLine

        public void drawLine(float x1,
                     float y1,
                     float x2,
                     float y2,
                     boolean optimize)
        Draw a line and create the corresponding gcode
        Parameters:
        x1 - origin x
        y1 - origin y
        x2 - destination x
        y2 - destination y
        optimize - it will try to optimize the drawing of the line according to the previous line drawn. Sometimes the logical is not right so set false if results are not like intended.

      • applyPushMatrix

        public void applyPushMatrix(float x1,
                            float y1,
                            float x2,
                            float y2,
                            boolean optimize)
        Same as draw line but including the rotation or translation passed before the function is called
        Parameters:
        x1 - origin x
        y1 - origin y
        x2 - destination x
        y2 - destination y
        applyTransformations - if true the rotation and translation will be applied. If false rotation and translation will be ignored.
        optimize - it will try to optimize the drawing of the line according to the previous line drawn. Sometimes the logical is not right so set false if results are not like intended.

      • addFilledShape

        public RShape addFilledShape(RShape down,
                             RShape up)
        This method is for simulating the drawing of a filled rectangle in white. It uses the geomerative library for calculating the intersect polygon of 2 shapes.
        Parameters:
        down - the shape on which we want to draw (shape to cut)
        up - the shape which should appear on front
        Returns:
        RShape

      • drawRShape

        public void drawRShape(RShape r,
                       float resolution)
        Parameters:
        r -
        resolution - it determines the quality of interpolation better is res il low i.e 0.01 but slower. It is also impacted by the resolution of RG from geomerative.
